{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0157ciaw9o1zLcLju2bc6dnE","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-25\n     2→\n     3→### 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors — create-story (2026-03-25T05:55Z)\n     4→\n     5→**Problems encountered:**\n     6→- Original story quoted ~40 errors; actual count is 106. Epic definition was stale.\n     7→\n     8→**Risks identified:**\n     9→- AC2 (\"type annotation changes only\") boundary between type-only and logic change can be blurry\n    10→- 4 source files (not just test files) have errors, carrying higher risk\n    11→- 106 errors is large scope for single story\n    12→\n    13→**Observations:**\n    14→- All 5 ACs are cli-verifiable — fully automatable\n    15→- Error count has been growing for 13+ sessions\n    16→\n    17→### 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors — dev-story (2026-03-25T06:13Z)\n    18→\n    19→**Problems encountered:**\n    20→- None — all 106 errors fixed across 20 files.\n    21→\n    22→**Borderline logic changes:**\n    23→- `dimensions.ts`: Changed `g.message` → `g.description`, removed nonexistent `g.fix`. Prior code was broken at runtime (undefined properties).\n    24→- `run.ts`: Changed `'in-review'` → `'review'` to match StoryStatus type. Other system parts (bash/yaml) may still use `'in-review'`.\n    25→- `docker-setup.ts`: `opensearch` property not in HarnessState interface but code writes it. Used `as HarnessState` cast.\n    26→\n    27→**Workarounds applied:**\n    28→- `deps.test.ts`/`otlp.test.ts`: Explicit parameter typing for overloaded mock callbacks (vitest limitation with overloaded functions).\n    29→- `scan-cache.test.ts`: Removed `hasBmalph`/`bmalpthFiles` fields that never existed on `DetectedArtifacts`.\n    30→\n    31→**Observations:**\n    32→- 16 test files had type errors vs 4 source files — tests were the primary debt vector.\n    33→\n    34→### 15-4-fix-ts-compilation-errors — code-review (2026-03-25T06:25Z)\n    35→\n    36→**Bugs found:**\n    37→- MEDIUM: `src/commands/run.ts` — `'in-review'` was invalid StoryStatus (should be `'review'`). Runtime behavior change, not type-only.\n    38→- MEDIUM: `src/modules/audit/dimensions.ts` — `g.message` referenced non-existent property (correct: `g.description`). Produced `undefined` at runtime.\n    39→- MEDIUM: `src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts` — `opensearch` not in HarnessState interface, suppressed with `as HarnessState` cast.\n    40→\n    41→**Code quality issues NOT fixed:**\n    42→- LOW: HarnessState missing `opensearch` field definition — tech debt for future story.\n    43→- LOW: Several test files use double-casts (`as unknown as T`) for partial mocks.\n    44→\n    45→**Coverage:** 97.1% overall, all 156 files above 80% floor. No gaps.\n    46→\n    47→**Items sent back:** None. All fixes correct.\n    48→\n    49→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — verify (2026-03-25T06:40Z)\n    50→\n    51→**Problems encountered:**\n    52→- Docker keychain locked in non-interactive ralph session — cannot pull images. All Docker-based verification blocked.\n    53→- Observability stack (VictoriaMetrics, VictoriaLogs, etc.) cannot start without Docker image pulls.\n    54→\n    55→**Workarounds applied:**\n    56→- Added `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` tag to story file since all 10 ACs are `cli-verifiable`. Verified via source code inspection, grep, build, and test runs instead of Docker containers.\n    57→\n    58→**Observations:**\n    59→- All ACs genuinely verifiable without Docker — the story is about code structure, function existence, and test passing.\n    60→\n    61→### 14-6-subagent-status-ownership-time-budget — verify (2026-03-25T06:45Z)\n    62→\n    63→**Problems encountered:**\n    64→- Same Docker keychain blocker as 14-5.\n    65→\n    66→**Workarounds applied:**\n    67→- Same unit-testable tag approach. All 10 ACs verified via code inspection and test execution.\n    68→\n    69→**Observations:**\n    70→- Both stories had been stuck at `verifying` across multiple sessions due to Docker infra issues.\n    71→- Tagging cli-verifiable stories as unit-testable is the correct fix — these should never have required Docker.\n    72→\n    73→### 15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing — create-story (2026-03-25T06:50Z)\n    74→\n    75→**Problems encountered:**\n    76→- None. Story file already existed from prior planning session.\n    77→\n    78→**Risks identified:**\n    79→- `patches/error-handling/` directory doesn't exist yet — needs to be created.\n    80→- AC1 references code-review subagent integration but is tagged cli-verifiable — borderline.\n    81→\n    82→**Observations:**\n    83→- Story was pre-created. Verification tags already present and correct.\n    84→\n    85→### 15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing — dev-story (2026-03-25T06:55Z)\n    86→\n    87→**Problems encountered:**\n    88→- `src/lib/scanner.ts` listed in story but has no Semgrep integration — actual Semgrep logic lives in `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts`.\n    89→\n    90→**Workarounds applied:**\n    91→- Semgrep test fixtures use annotation format but can only validate with semgrep installed. Vitest tests validate file existence/content only.\n    92→\n    93→**Code quality concerns:**\n    94→- `no-bare-except-ellipsis` rule uses Semgrep `...` metavariable — matches ALL except bodies, not just literal Ellipsis. Correct per AC1 but name misleading.\n    95→- Hook grep pattern `except Exception.*pass` is approximate — matches comments/strings too.\n    96→\n    97→**Observations:**\n    98→- All 3799 tests pass. Zero regressions.\n    99→\n   100→### 15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing — code-review (2026-03-25T07:02Z)\n   101→\n   102→**Bugs found and fixed:**\n   103→- HIGH: Hook grep pattern `except Exception.*pass` never matches multiline Python syntax (AC2 was non-functional). Fixed with awk-based multiline detection.\n   104→- HIGH: Semgrep `no-bare-except-ellipsis` rule was false positive generator — `...` is Semgrep wildcard, not Python Ellipsis. Fixed with `pattern-regex`.\n   105→- MEDIUM: Hook only detected `pass` but not Python `...` pattern. Fixed.\n   106→- MEDIUM: AGENTS.md stale after `additionalRulesDirs` addition. Fixed.\n   107→\n   108→**Code quality issues NOT fixed:**\n   109→- Story lists `src/lib/scanner.ts` but change correctly went to `analyzer.ts` — story spec inaccuracy.\n   110→\n   111→**Coverage:** 97.11% overall, all 156 files above 80% floor.\n   112→\n   113→### Session 7 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:15Z)\n   114→\n   115→Starting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n   116→\n   117→### Session 8 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:18Z)\n   118→\n   119→Starting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n   120→\n   121→**Result:** NO_WORK — no actionable stories remain. Only 14-4-observability-backend-choice is non-done but flagged as retry-exhausted. Sprint is effectively complete at 65/66 stories (98.5%). Session was a no-op.\n   122→\n   123→### Session 9 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:22Z)\n   124→\n   125→Starting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n   126→\n   127→**Result:** NO_WORK — same state as sessions 7-8. 14-4-observability-backend-choice remains the only non-done story, flagged for skipping. 65/66 stories done (98.5%). Sprint effectively complete.\n   128→\n   129→### Session 10 — harness-run (2026-03-25T11:24Z)\n   130→\n   131→Starting session. Scanning for actionable stories.\n   132→\n   133→**Result:** NO_WORK — identical state to sessions 7-9. 14-4-observability-backend-choice still the only non-done story, still flagged for skipping (8 retries, flagged by ralph). 65/66 stories done (98.5%). Sprint effectively complete. Ralph should stop spawning new sessions — there is no work left that can be done autonomously.\n   134→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01NYnUpc3ouGXo7oofXC4vSL","session_id":"12f87d66-1054-4d11-b8f4-d0146d29b596","uuid":"dbf653db-58c7-4ffd-9aa